abstract = {Usual listings of top 10 smart cities in the world invariably include “usual suspects” such as London, Paris, New York, Barcelona, major cities in developed countries with plenty of resources, and a long tradition of planning and management. You read references in preceding chapters from the 21@ in the old Poblenou in Barcelona, the Broadway resignification and the High Line in New York City, the Leicester Square project in London, the historic planning of Paris, etc. But there are other interesting examples in other cities that show striking Humane and Sustainable Smart City (HSSC) characteristics. And observe that some of the megacities today are in emerging countries and a few more will be added to the list in the near future. This chapter explores 30 real cases of places in the world that, either as cities that are exemplary textbook smarter cities, or boroughs or projects that exhibit at least one feature of a future HSSC. Each case study is comprised of: project description, the most striking dimension of the project, the current situation, benefits for the citizen and possible drawbacks, and the project’s future plans. The places selected include cities from all over the world and explore the eight dimensions of HSSC described in Chapter 4, The Eight Dimensions of a More Humane and Sustainable Smart City.}
