abstract = {As the world is becoming increasingly urban, it is also becoming increasingly metropolitan. Cities have expanded outward, and satellite cities and towns have over time become more closely connected to an urban center. This chapter outlines how cities in a metropolitan area can benefit from collaboration on their smart city developments through an intermunicipal forum or council. Opportunities that can be seized jointly for efficiency/cost-effectiveness for all include strategic planning; area-wide data collection for planning; capturing economies of scale through joint procurement, research, and training; piloting technologies; and creating a joint body for their smart city development, possibly even functioning as a “control center” for some implemented applications. It may involve pooling of funds for a facility or equipment for shared use. The chapter also highlights more comprehensive metropolitan governance models applied internationally, through which smart city matters can be addressed, and obstacles that need to be overcome for effective collaboration among local governments. It concludes with a summary of a systematic approach along the lines of a smart city development framework outlined by the World Bank for cities in developing countries.}
